review_blob: Pours a slightly hazy golden with a small white frothy head. Aroma of citrus and some malts. Flavour is slightly sweet, hops and some fruit.
Pours a light gold with a thin white head. Aroma of mild fruits, weak hops. Flavour is much the same but a bit thin. Didnt enjoy this.
Pours a dark brown with a slight red and a tan foam head. Aroma of roasted malts and some coffee notes. Taste is malts, chocolate, coffee and a slight hint of liquorice. Smooth.

Pours a clear, slightly dark orange with a good sized off white head. Aroma of mango, malts and pine. Taste is bitter with some nice malty/caramel notes. Doesnt taste as strong as the 9.2% would suggest.

Pours a dark amber/red with a big off white head. Head doesnt last long. Aroma is filled with malts and pine. Taste is quite strong/boozy with lots of bitterness and malts. Hints of orange coming through as well.
Pours black with a medium tan head. Aroma of black forrest/dark berries and roasted malts. Flavour is slightly sweet, malty and a hint of chocolate. Decent!

Pours a dark amber with a average foam head. Aroma is malty with a hint of fruit. Flavour, again, is some malts but lacking some oomph. Will have lost a bit of flavour over time as Ive had it a while. An alright beer that probably benefits from drinking fresh.

Bottle. Pours a hazy yellow with a big foam head that doesnt last long. Aroma is filled with tropical fruits. This smells amazing. Flavour is hoppy with plenty of tropical fruit. Lovely bitter finish. A great beer!
Bottle. Pours black with a small tan head. Aroma is roasted malts and coffee. Taste is slightly sweet with coffee, chocolate and malts. A fine coffee stout.

Pours a cloudy amber with a decent sized white head. Aroma is packed with orange and pine. Flavour is bitter with plenty of fruit (orange) and faint hints of malts. Not too boozy for being 9%. Excellent beer.
Bottle. Pours clear gold with a small white head. Aroma is lacking. There are hints of hops, pine and fruit but its weak. Flavour has some tropical fruit but its thin. Disappointing.
Pours a dark brown with a small beige head. Aroma is weak but has hints of roasted malts and caramel. Flavour is very thin with small malty notes coming through. Watery and lacking.
Pours a dark black/brown with a small off white head. Lovely aroma filled with coffee, roasted malts and hints of chocolate. Flavour is just as good with much of the same. An excellent beer.
Tasting at BrewDog AGM. Pours a clear gold with a small white head. Aroma is quite fruity with some lemon and a hint of spice. Flavour is sweet with the hops, citrus and floral notes coming through.
Pours a clear gold with a small white head. Aroma is fantastic. Lots of citrus hops. Flavour is full of citrus hops with hints of caramel and malts. What a beer!

On tap at BrewDog AGM. Pours a dark red/brown with an off white head. Aroma has hints of coffee, rum, chocolate. Flavour is sweet and boozy. Described as liquid tiramisu by BrewDog, they are not wrong.
Tasting at BrewDog AGM. Pours a cloudy red/peach. Aroma is filled with fruitiness. The taste is sweet and quite sharp. The berry flavours come right through. Quite tart.
BrewDog AGM tasting. Pours a hazy brown/red. Aroma of rye, caramel and oak. Flavour is biter with some caramel coming through with lovely oak notes from the barrel.
beer_name: BrewDog Barrel Aged Albino Squid Assassin

review_blob: Pours a hazy red/amber with a beige head. Aroma of citrus hops and some malts. Flavour is full of malts, caramel, hops and citrus. A tasty beer.

Draft. Poured a deep black with a medium sized tan head. Aroma is roasted malts, chocolate and smalll coffee notes. Flavour is slightly sweet and bitter with the chocolate, caramel, coffee and roasted malts coming through.

Pours a slight hazy amber with a frothy head. Sweet citrus and tropical aroma. Taste is very bitter with a slight tang to it. The sweetness comes through along with the hops and hints of malt. Had some excellent beers recently that have all been better than this. Not a bad beer though and would have it again.

Very generic lager this one. Slight metallic aroma with a bland taste. Not much coming through in this one at all. Will appeal to lager drinkers and a better option to the mass produced lager on tap elsewhere but thats about it.
UPDATED: APR 12, 2016
Pours a clear dark amber with a small off white head. Aroma is malty with hints of caramel. Taste is strong hops, malty with a nice sweetness in there. Nice bitter aftertaste as well.

Pours a jet black with a small off white head. Aroma of coffee, roasted malts and a hint of chocolate. Taste is much the same which is lovely. This is a very drinkable beer and it is quite light. Had to get another after I finished the first.

Pours a deep amber with a decent white head. Aroma has lots of smoke and peat with a woodiness to it. Flavour is very much the same which for some will be a lovely drink and others not so much. A decent enough beer but just not one for me.

Pours a nice gold with a frothy white head that fades fast. Strong aroma of peach and pine with an earthiness to it. Flavour is heavy hops with hints of the gin and rye coming through. Strong flavour and overall a fine beer!
Pours a deep black with a slight redness to it. Large frothy head that lasts well. Aroma is roasted malts with some caramel and hints of coffee. Flavour has the malts with some chocolate notes.
Pours a dark copper. Aroma of malts with hints of toffee. Flavour is much the same with not much going on. Very thin and boring.
Pours a deep black with a small tan head. An amazing, massive coffee aroma. Flavour is heavy on the roasted coffee with malt notes. I love coffee, I love beer, I love this!
Pours a dark brown with a big off white head. Aroma is roasted malts with hints of coffee. Flavour has some fruit notes hidden behind the roasted malts and hints of chocolate and coffee.
Pours a very dark brown with a small head. Aroma is fantastic. Huge on the coconut. Flavour is like liquid bounty. Wow!
beer_name: Oskar Blues / Shamrock Death By Coconut

review_blob: Pours a light gold with a small white head. Aroma is very fruity with hints of pineapple and mango. Flavour is very bitter with citrus hops. A fine beer.

Pours a slight hazy amber with a big frothy white head. Aroma is big on the grapefruit with notes of pine with the hops coming through. Flavour is a slight sweet citrus with malt notes. A lovely smooth bitter finish on this. Great beer.

Bottle. Pours a dark amber with a lasting off white head. Aroma is of malts and some caramel. Taste is a bit watery but much the same as the aroma with a dry and slightly bitter finish. Nothing exciting going on here.

Pours black with a small tan head. Aroma is strong roasted malts with a heavy hit of coffee. Taste is slightly sweet with hints of chocolate amongst the coffee/espresso notes. Very smooth to drink with a lovely warm bitter espresso finish.
beer_name: Beavertown / Prairie Artisanal Ales / Caravan Coffee Barrel Aged Spresso

review_blob: Pours a dark red with a cream head. Aroma is heavy smoked malts. Flavour is again, heavy smoked with an almost meaty taste. Not one for me.

Bottle. Pours a slightly hazy amber with an average off white head. The aroma is a wonderful mix of citrus and tropical fruits with the hops and hint of malts coming through. Taste has hints of caramel and malts with some pine. Excellent beer. Just wish I had it closer to the bottling date.

Bottle of 12.25.15. Pours a deep golden colour with a white head. The aroma is full of citrus/grapefruit with a hint of pine. Taste is, again, citrus with lots of hops and a freshness to it all. It all ends on a big bitter finish. A fine beer worthy of its high rating.

Bottle. Pours amber with a large frothy head. Aroma is light malts with some sweetness but nothing great going on. Flavour is similar with the malts coming through. Not a big fan of lagers but I would say this was one of the better ones for me.
Bottle. Pours black with a tan head. Aroma is of roasted malts, coffee and chocolate. Taste is slightly sweet with lots of dark chocolate and espresso.

Bottle. Pours black with a small off white head that quickly vanishes. It has a fruity hops aroma with a hint of berries coming through. Roasted malts and more berry comes through in the taste. Really nice black IPA.

Bottle. Pours almost black with a small, short lasting, cream head. Lots of coffee in the aroma here with hints of chocolate. Taste is more coffee with malts and notes of caramel. Smooth to drink and goes down a bit too easy. Could easily drink a few of these in a row.Earlier Rating: 12/3/2015 Total Score: 3.8Tap. Pours a deep black with a creamy off white head. Aroma is of roasted malts, milk chocolate and coffee. A very creamy beer with pretty much zero carbonation. Taste is milky with chocolate and subtle vanilla notes coming through. A lovely smooth stout.
Bottle. Pours a hazy orange with an average foamy head. Aroma is citrus hops with a little malt. Flavour is much the same with a nice bitter finish.
Bottle. Pours a slight hazy amber with a large off white, frothy head. Aroma has orange and lemon with floral and pine notes through it. Taste is more of the citrus with some malts.
Bottle. Pours hazy orange with a large frothy head. Aroma is fruity/peachy and hoppy. Taste is similar with a lovely bitter end. Very enjoyable.
UPDATED: DEC 31, 2015
Bottle. Pours a dark amber with a short lasting tan head. Aroma is malty with hints of caramel. Has a sweet malty taste. Dry finish. Nothing special but not bad either.

Bottle. Pours a clear and light yellow with a foamy head. The aroma is excellent. Full of fruity/citrus/tropical hops. A real mix. Flavour is a slightly sweet citrus with a nice bitterness. Really enjoyable IPA.

Bottle. Pours black with a large cream coloured frothy head. Aroma is slightly burnt malts with coffee and an earthiness to it. Smooth on the taste with a flavour of malts with hints of chocolate and coffee. Dry and bitter finish.
